message: add travic.yml and improve server-side rendering
grunt build changes and server render improvements
pushState improvements and bump version to 0.1.8
fixes, improvements and bump version to 0.2.1
implement async requests and bump version to 0.2.4
server-side rendering fixes & bump version to 0.2.7
little improvements and bump version to 0.3.0

Updated dev-dependencies.

src/.jshintrc Changed latedef to false. otherwise jshint complains about some
defined functions and objects that aren't wrong in our case.

build/tasks/debug Updated to the new Parse5 API.

lib/blocks/jsdebug Updated to new highlightjs names.

package.json Updated all the dev-dependencies.

First (git) actions for CI build releases. <WIP>

Added grunt tasks:
- 'publish' which checks for version changes in the
package.json in the last master commit and if invokes the grunt tasks
'build-only' and 'publish-post-build'.
- 'build-only' like 'full-build' but without the test part as travis
  already run the tasks.
- 'publish-post-build' adds a commit for the build files, creates a tag
  with the version.
  TODO: publish to npm.

Adds dev dependencies: nodegit and npm-utils.

Added dev-dependencie "github" for easy github api access.
now Building a commit history and adding it to the release.

Should be able to push releases to github.

Replaced (most) REST-Calls to github with GraphQL.

Way less requests.
The GraphQL is still in alpha, that's why some things are as they are
and it's possible that it fails, but that shouldn't be a bug deal since
I'm able to fix those fail in like no time manually.

Removed jquery, jasmine & jasmine-jquery from lib folder and adedd the
same as a dev dependencie.

I think thoose external dependencies should be managed by npm as it's
easier.

Added karma-coverage and config for it.

Coverage report can be generated with ``grunt test:coverage``.
That will create a "coverage" folder in the project root.
